title: G20 leaders ignore Trump boycott to reaffirm commitment to climate action | ABC NEWS
description: G20 leaders have ignored US President Donald Trump’s boycott of the summit and signed a declaration to strengthen the Paris climate agreement and amplify support for free trade.  The US leader refused to attend the meeting in South Africa, urging his counterparts not to condone any action at the talks.  However, Australian Prime Minister Anthony Albanese hailed the spirit of unity among world leaders at the event in Johannesburg. title: Greens Senator Sarah Hanson-Young on Labor's environmental reforms and COP31 | Insiders | ABC NEWS
description: David Speers interviews Greens senator Sarah Hanson-Young on Labor's new environmental reforms - the EPBC. The pair unpack native forest logging concessions, and what the Greens want in exchange for their support for the government's bill.  They discuss the approval process for coal and gas projects and the powers of the proposed EPA, as well as COP31 and the government'ss social media ban for children. title: Tropical Cyclone Fina forecast to ease before hitting northern WA coast | ABC News
description: The Top End is bracing for more heavy rain and gusty winds as Tropical Cyclone Fina tracks further away from Darwin.  The Bureau of Meteorology is forecasting the storm to intensify into a category 4 system offshore but weaken before it reaches Western Australia’s Kimberley coast.  Senior meteorologist Dean Narramore is urging Top end residents to remain vigilant despite easing conditions as some areas are facing risks of flash flooding. title: Tropical Cyclone Fina leaves Darwin residents to assess damage | ABC NEWS
description: Residents in the Top End are assessing damage from Cyclone Fina, which passed just north of Darwin as a category 3 system last night. title: Severe Tropical Cyclone Fina leaves a path of destruction in her wake | ABC NEWS
description: 00:00 Severe Tropical Cyclone Fina has passed Darwin and the Tiwi Islands at category three strength, with the weather system's gale-force winds leaving a path of destruction as it continues west into the ocean. Fina was the Northern Territory's strongest cyclone to pass Darwin since the deadly Cyclone Tracy in 1974. The system was also more powerful than Cyclone Marcus, which passed Darwin as a category two in 2018. Now tracking west-south-west, Severe TC Fina is picking up strength over the Timor Sea and is expected to move over the top of Western Australia in the coming days. 02:11 ABC reporter Olivana Lathouris on trying to get a sense of when things will return to normal. 03:12 Despite the massive clean-up ahead for Darwin, the city's resilience has shone through as locals pick up the pieces ready to move on. 05:20 With power still down across parts of Darwin, Power and Water crews are working to restore as many homes as possible.  08:22 ABC meteorologist Nate Byrne on experiencing his first cyclone, and Fina's path from here.
